<body>
    <form action="/gokarna" method="get">
    <div id="nav">
        <form action="/search" method="get">
          <p id="p1">Gokarna</p>
         </form>
         <hr style="border-color:black;position:relative;top: 70px;">
         <div id="i1">
            <img id="apimg" src="https://dynamic-media-cdn.tripadvisor.com/media/photo-o/03/53/5e/7f/om-beach.jpg?w=1000&h=-1&s=1">
        </div>
        <br><br><br><br><br>
        <div id="i2">
            <h2><strong><center>INFORMATION</center></strong></h2>
            <hr style="width: 950px;height: 1.5px;background-color: black;"><br>
            <p>If you love palm trees, pristine blue seas and clean golden sand, you must visit Gokarna for your next holiday. Initially, it was a popular Hindu pilgrimage town, but it has become a famous place for beach lovers in recent years. It has some of the best beaches in entire Karnataka. <br>

                Best Time to Visit- October to March <br>
                Ideal Vacation Duration- 2-3 days <br>
                Average expenses: Starting from ₹25,000 (4 days/3 nights) <br>
                Places to Visit- Mahabaleshwara Temple, Om beach, Paradise beach, Kudle Beach, Gokarna Beach <br>
                Things to Do- Go for beach trekking, eat at Namaste Café, try various water sports, explore Mirjan Fort, and go on pilgrimage. <br>
                </p>
            
        </div>
        <div id="i3">
            <center><h2>WEATHER</h2></center><br>
            <hr style="width: 360px;height: 1.5px;background-color: black;">
            <div class="icon">
            <h1><%=temp%>°C</h1><img src="/day/default.png" alt="" srcset="" id="image">
            </div>
            <h2 class="climate"><%=climate%></h2>
                <h2>Humidity : <%=humidity%>%<br><br>Wind Speed : <%=windspeed%>kmph</h2>
        </div>
        <div id="i4">
            <center><h2>TRANSPORTATION</h2></center><br>
            <hr style="width: 360px;height: 1.5px;background-color: black;"><br>
            <p> <img src="https://img.icons8.com/?size=1x&id=oOAYqE64W2MO&format=png" height="25px" width="25px" alt="">&nbsp;&nbsp;By Air-Nearest airport is Goa International Airport which is 106 km (3 to 5 hours) away.<br><br>
                <img src="https://img.icons8.com/?size=1x&id=d8MqKVWJkyqN&format=png" alt="" height="25px" width="25px">&nbsp;&nbsp; By Train-A small railway station is 10 km away from the main city of Gokarna. The nearest well-connected station is at a 20 km distance in Ankola.<br><br>
                <img src="https://img.icons8.com/?size=1x&id=f42OOoV1ACzO&format=png" alt="" height="25px" width="25px">&nbsp;&nbsp;By Road- You will find direct buses and taxis to travel to Bengaluru and Mangalore.</p>
        </div>
    </form>
    <script>
        
        let image=document.getElementById("image");

        let climate=document.querySelector(".climate").textContent;
        if(climate=="Mist"){
            image.src="/day/Mist.png"
        }
        if(climate=="Patchy rain possible"){
            image.src="/day/Patchy.png"
        }
        if(climate=="Moderate rain"){
            image.src="/day/Moderate.png"
        }
        if(climate=="Light rain shower"){
            image.src="/day/patchy.png"
        }
        if(climate=="Partly cloudy"){
            image.src="/day/default.png"
        }
        if(climate=="Cloudy"){
            image.src="/day/Cloudy.png"
        }
        if(climate=="Overcast"){
            image.src="/day/Cloudy.png"
        }
        if(climate=="Sunny"){
            image.src="/day/Sunny.png"
        }
        if(climate=="Clear"){
            image.src="/day/Sunny.png"
        }
        if(climate=="Thundery outbreaks possible"){
            image.src="/day/Thunderstorm.png"
        }
        if(climate=="Fog"){
            image.src="/day/Fog.png"
        }
        if(climate=="Light rain"){
            image.src="/day/Patchy.png"
        }
        if(climate=="Moderate or heavy rain shower"){
            image.src="/day/Heavy.png"
        }
        if(climate=="Light drizzle"){
            image.src="/day/Drizzle.png"
        }
    
</script>
